findings.suggestion:
Validate each entry's resolved path against destDir before opening the output stream. Reject entries whose canonical path does not start with the canonical path of destDir. Also create parent directories for file entries explicitly, since the upstream code assumes directory entries precede file entries (not guaranteed by the ZIP format).

```kotlin
val destDirCanonical = destDir.canonicalPath
while (zipEntry != null) {
  val outFile = File(destDir, zipEntry.name)
  val outCanonical = outFile.canonicalPath
  if (!outCanonical.startsWith(destDirCanonical + File.separator) && outCanonical != destDirCanonical) {
    throw IOException("ZipSlip blocked: ${zipEntry.name}")
  }
  if (zipEntry.isDirectory) {
    outFile.mkdirs()
  } else {
    outFile.parentFile?.mkdirs()
    FileOutputStream(outFile).use { bos ->
      var len: Int
      while (zipIn.read(unzipBuffer).also { len = it } > 0) bos.write(unzipBuffer, 0, len)
    }
  }
  zipIn.closeEntry()
  zipEntry = zipIn.nextEntry
}
```
